{"title_page": "Halitha Shameem", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Halitha Shameem\n| image              = https://twitter.com/halithashameem/photo.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_place        = [[Dharapuram]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| occupation         = [[Film director]]<br />[[Screenwriter]]<br />[[Film Editing]]\n| years_active       = 2014\u2013present\n| children           = \n}}\n'''Halitha Shameem''' is an [[Indian film]] director, screenwriter and editor who predominantly works in [[Tamil cinema]].<ref>{{cite web |title=All you want to know about #HalithaShameem |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/celebs/halitha-shameem.html |website=FilmiBeat |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> She worked as an assistant director with [[Pushkar-Gayathri]] and [[Mishkin]]. In 2014, she made her [[Tamil cinema]] debut with ''[[Poovarasam Peepee]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nHalitha was born in [[Dharapuram]], [[Tamil Nadu]]. She moved to Chennai to pursue opportunities in a creative career.\n\n==Career==\nAfter assisting in movies such as [[Oram Po]], she debuted as a director with [[Poovarasam Peepee]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018I love doing films with big stars, but I love introducing new talents more\u2019 - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-love-doing-films-with-big-stars-but-i-love-introducing-new-talents-more/articleshow/73929687.cms |website=The Times of India |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> After a gap of more than 5 years, she then directed the critically and commercially successful [[anthology film]] [[Sillu Karupatti]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=S |first1=Srivatsan |title=\u2018Sillu Karupatti\u2019 movie review: Life is like a box of chocolates |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/sillu-karupatti-movie-review-life-is-like-a-box-of-chocolates/article30410499.ece |website=The Hindu |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en-IN |date=27 December 2019}}</ref> She has now completed filming of her next movie ''[[Aela (film)|Aelay]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Exciting update on Sillukaruppatti director's next movie! - Tamil News |url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/sillukaruppatti-director-next-movie-update-announced-tamil-news-252198 |website=IndiaGlitz.com |accessdate=18 February 2020 |date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! [[Film director|Director]]\n! [[Screenwriter]]\n! [[Language]]\n! Notes\n\n|-\n|2014 || ''[[Poovarasam Peepee]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || Tamil ||\n|-\n|2019 || ''[[Sillu Karupatti]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || Tamil|| \n|-\n|2020\n|''Aelay''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n|Tamil\n| Filming completed\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Artists from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Tamil screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Tamil film directors]]\n[[Category:Indian women film directors]]\n[[Category:Indian women screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Women artists from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian film directors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian women artists]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Women writers from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Writers from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian women writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Halitha Shameem\n| image              = https://twitter.com/halithashameem/photo.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_place        = [[Dharapuram]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| occupation         = [[Film director]]<br />[[Screenwriter]]<br />[[Film Editing]]\n| years_active       = 2014\u2013present\n| children           = \n}}\n'''Halitha Shameem''' is an [[Indian film]] director, screenwriter and editor who predominantly works in [[Tamil cinema]].<ref>{{cite web |title=All you want to know about #HalithaShameem |url=https://www.filmibeat.com/celebs/halitha-shameem.html |website=FilmiBeat |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> She worked as an assistant director with [[Pushkar-Gayathri]] and [[Mishkin]]. In 2014, she made her [[Tamil cinema]] debut with ''[[Poovarasam Peepee]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nHalitha was born in [[Dharapuram]], [[Tamil Nadu]]. She moved to Chennai to pursue opportunities in a creative career.\n\n==Career==\nAfter assisting in movies such as [[Oram Po]], she debuted as a director with [[Poovarasam Peepee]] in 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018I love doing films with big stars, but I love introducing new talents more\u2019 - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-love-doing-films-with-big-stars-but-i-love-introducing-new-talents-more/articleshow/73929687.cms |website=The Times of India |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> After a gap of more than 5 years, she then directed the critically and commercially successful [[anthology film]] [[Sillu Karupatti]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=S |first1=Srivatsan |title=\u2018Sillu Karupatti\u2019 movie review: Life is like a box of chocolates |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/sillu-karupatti-movie-review-life-is-like-a-box-of-chocolates/article30410499.ece |website=The Hindu |accessdate=18 February 2020 |language=en-IN |date=27 December 2019}}</ref> She has now completed filming of her next movie ''[[Aela (film)|Aelay]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Exciting update on Sillukaruppatti director's next movie! - Tamil News |url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/sillukaruppatti-director-next-movie-update-announced-tamil-news-252198 |website=IndiaGlitz.com |accessdate=18 February 2020 |date=28 January 2020}}</ref>  \n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n