a's first-, third-, and seventh-round selections ([[#Pick 31|31st]], [[#Pick 95|95th]], and [[#Pick 249|249th]]).<ref name=\"2017TradeTracker\"/>}} |cfb page exists=yes }}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |compensatory=yes |round=3 | picknum=106 | team=Seattle Seahawks | first=Amara | last=Darboh |dab= | position=WR | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note= |cfb page exists= yes}}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |round=4 | picknum=120 | team=Minnesota Vikings | first=Ben | last=Gedeon |dab= | position=LB | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note= |cfb page exists=yes }}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |compensatory=yes |round=4 | picknum=138 | team=Cincinnati Bengals | first=Ryan | last=Glasgow |dab= | position=DT | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note= |cfb page exists=yes }}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |compensatory=yes |round=4 | picknum=139 | team=Kansas City Chiefs | first=Jehu | last=Chesson |dab= | position=WR | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note=from [[2017 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland]] via [[2017 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia]] and [[2017 Minnesota Vikings season|Minnesota]]&nbsp;{{refn|{{Anchor|2016NumberTwoPick}}'''No. 139: Cleveland \u2192 Philadelphia (PD).'''<ref name=2016NumberTwoPick>{{cite news |last=Rosenthal |first=Gregg |title=Eagles acquire No. 2 overall draft pick from Browns |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000654501/article/eagles-acquire-no-2-overall-draft-pick-from-browns |website=NFL.com |date=April 20, 2016 |accessdate=April 20, 2016}}</ref>}} |cfb page exists=yes }}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |round=5 | picknum=145 | team=Denver Broncos | first=Jake | last=Butt |dab= | position=TE | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note=from [[2017 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland]] |cfb page exists=yes }}\n\n{{NFLDraft-row |draftyear= 2017 |round=6 | picknum=197 | team=New York Jets | first=Jeremy | last=Clark |dab=Jeremy Clark (American football) | position=CB | collegeyear=2016 | college=Michigan | collegeteam=Michigan Wolverines | collegelink=Michigan | probowl= |note=from [[2017 Arizona Cardinals season|Arizona]] via [[2017 Chicago Bears season|Chicago]] and [[2017 Los Angeles Rams season|LA Rams]]&nbsp;{{refn|{{Anchor|BakerTrade}}'''No. 197: Arizona \u2192 Chicago (D).''' [[2017 Chicago Bears season|Chicago]] traded their second- and seventh-round selections ([[#Pick 36|36th]] and [[#Pick 221|221st]]) to [[2017 Arizona Cardinals season|Arizona]] in exchange for Arizona's second-, fourth-, and sixth-round selections ([[#Pick 45|45th]], [[#Pick 119|119th]], and [[#Pick 197|197th]]) as well as a fourth-round selection in [[2018 NFL Draft|2018]].<ref name=\"2017TradeTracker\"/>}} |cfb page exists=yes}}\n\n{{NFLDraft-footer}}\n\nMichigan set a program record with 11 NFL Draft selections, surpassing the previous record of 10, which was set in [[1972 Michigan Wolverines football team|1972]] and [[1974 Michigan Wolverines football team|1974]]. Nine of this year's selections came in the first four rounds, setting another program record. It was also the most draftees in the 2017 NFL Draft by any school.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-M Leads All Programs in Players Picked in 2017 NFL Draft|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=April 29, 2017|date=April 29, 2017|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/042917abg.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Michigan Sets Record on Day Three of NFL Draft|publisher=CBS Interactive|work=MGoBlue.com|accessdate=April 29, 2017|date=April 29, 2017|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/042917aag.html}}</ref>\n\n==Roster==\n{{American football roster/Hea