udinal research (in collaboration with Professor [[Birna Arnbj\u00f6rnsd\u00f3ttir]]) on the status of English in Iceland.<ref>University of Iceland. (2018). [https://english.hi.is/news/the_impact_of_english_on_the_icelandic_speech_community The impact of English on the Icelandic speech community]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref>\n \nHafd\u00eds has taken part in many European development projects related to teaching, in addition to research projects on teacher education. She has worked enthusiastically on teachers' continuous education and has held many courses and workshops for that purpose. She has given lectures on her research at a great number of international conferences. Her writings have appeared in both Iceland and other countries in book chapters and peer-reviewed articles.<ref name=\"Hafd\u00eds\" />\n\n== Other work and projects ==\nHafd\u00eds has held various positions of confidentiality in Iceland and abroad, under the auspices of the Ministry of Education, Science and Culture and  the University of Iceland. She was on a collaborative committee on continuous education of upper secondary school teachers, where she represented the University of Iceland (1992\u20132009). The committee's function was to formulate policy on the continuing education of upper secondary school teachers and allocate funds to upper secondary schools for continuing education.<ref name=\"Hafd\u00eds\" /> Hafd\u00eds sat on a committee on European Teachers\u2019 Education 2010 after the Ministry of Education, Science and Culture nominated her for the period 2006 to 2008. The University of Iceland nominated Hafd\u00eds to sit on a committee, under the auspices of the Minister of Education, Science and Culture. The committee's function was to set out proposals on the future organisation of the curriculum for teachers 2005\u20132006.<ref>Menntam\u00e1lar\u00e1\u00f0uneyti\u00f0. (2006). [https://www.stjornarradid.is/media/menntamalaraduneyti-media/media/ritogskyrslur/framtidarskipan_kennaramenntunar.pdf Till\u00f6gur starfsh\u00f3ps um framt\u00ed\u00f0arskipan kennaramenntunar]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref> She was UI's representative on a national committee advising the Minister of Education, Science and Culture. The question was whether to introduce the use of the European portfolio in  language teaching (ETM) in Icelandic schools from 2002 to 2006.<ref>Menntam\u00e1lastofnun. [https://mms.is/namsefni/evropska-tungumalamappan-fyrir-framhaldsskolastigEvr\u00f3pska tungum\u00e1lamappan fyrir framhaldssk\u00f3lastig]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref><ref>Menntam\u00e1lastofnun. [https://mms.is/namsefni/evropska-tungumalamappan-fyrir-grunnskolastig Evr\u00f3pska tungum\u00e1lamappan fyrir grunnsk\u00f3lastig]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref> From 2003 to 2009, she sat on the executive committee of the International Study Association of Teachers and Teaching (ISATT).<ref>[https://www.isatt.net/ International Study Association of Teachers and Teaching]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref> This is an international association of researchers studying teachers and teaching. In addition, Hafd\u00eds sat on an advisory committee, The UK Council for Graduate Education,<ref>[http://www.ukcge.ac.uk/about-ukcge/ukcge.aspx UK Council for Graduate Education]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref> from 2006 to 2010. She was also one of the founders and the first chairman of the Language Teachers Association in Iceland (ST\u00cdL) from 1985 to 1989.<ref>P\u00e9tur Rasmussen. (2014). [http://timarit.is/view_page_init.jsp?pageId=6089379 M\u00e9r hefur alltaf fundist danska svo fallegt tunugm\u00e1l]. M\u00e1lfr\u00ed\u00f0ur. T\u00edmarit Samtaka tungum\u00e1lakennara, 30(1): 5-9.</ref> \n\n== Acknowledgements ==\nIn 2016, Hafd\u00eds received an award from the international language teachers\u2019 association \u201cF\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale des Professeurs de Langues Vivantes\u201d (FIPLV) for her contribution to language teaching and research.<ref>ST\u00cdL \u2013 Samt\u00f6k tungum\u00e1lakennara \u00e1 \u00cdslandi \u2013 The Association of Language Teachers in Iceland. [http://stil-is.weebly.com/ Hei\u00f0ursver\u00f0laun FIPLV]. Retrieved March 11, 2020.</ref> \n\n== Selected writings ==\n=== Articles ===\n*Hafd\u00eds Ingvarsd\u00f3ttir (2006). [http://hdl.handle.net/1946/8638 \u201e\u2026eins og \u00fever geit \u00ed gir\u00f0ingu\u201c Vi\u00f0horf kennara til breytinga \u00e1 kennsluh\u00e1ttum]. In \u00dalfar Hauksson (Ritstj.), Ranns\u00f3knir \u00ed f\u00e9lagsv\u00edsindum VII (pp. 351\u2013364). Reykjav\u00edk: H\u00e1sk\u00f3la\u00fatg\u00e1fan.  \n*Hafd\u00eds Ingvarsd\u00f3ttir (2013). [https://www.degruyter.com/view/j/jelf.2013.2.issue-1/jelf-2013-0006/jelf-2013-0006.xml ELF and academic writing: a perspective from the Expanding Circle]. Journal of English as a Lingua Franca. JELF. De Gruyter.\n*Hafd\u00eds Ingvarsd\u00f3ttir (2018). [http://netla.hi.is/serrit/2018/framhaldskolinn_brennidepli/03.pdf Kennsluh\u00e6ttir spegla\u00f0ir \u00ed lj\u00f3si sj\u00e1lfr\u00e6\u00f0is: Vir\u00f0ing, \u00e1byrg\u00f0 og traust]. Netla \u2013 Veft\u00edmarit um uppeldi og menntun. S\u00e9rrit 2018 \u2013 Framhaldsk\u00f3linn \u00ed brennidepli. Menntav\u00edsindasvi\u00f0 H\u00e1sk\u00f3la \u00cdslands, pp. 1\u201314.\n\n=== Books ===\n*Birna  Arnbj\u00f6rnsd\u00f3ttir og Hafd\u00eds Ingvarsd\u00f3ttir (ritstj.) (2007). [http://haskolautgafan.hi.is/teaching_and_learning_english_in_iceland Teaching and learning English in Iceland. In honour of Au\u00f0ur Torfad\u00f3ttir]. Reykjav\u00edk: Stofnun Vigd\u00edsar Finnbogad\u00f3ttur/H\u00e1sk\u00f3la\u00fatg\u00e1fan\n*Birna Arnbj\u00f6rnsd\u00f3ttir og Hafd\u00eds Ingvarsd\u00f3ttir (eds.). (2017). [https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-3-319-67804-7 Language Development across the Life Span: The Impact of English on Education and Work in Iceland].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n\n[[Category:University of Iceland faculty]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Iceland alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Copenhagen alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century Icelandic women writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hafd%C3%ADs_Ingvarsd%C3%B3ttir"}
{"title_page": "Alexander Elder", "text_new": "{{about||the nineteenth-century settler and politician in colonial South Australia|Alexander Lang Elder|the Northern Irish footballer|Alex Elder}}\n<!-- Unsourced image removed: [[File:Alexander_elder.jpg|300px|right]] -->\n'''Alexander Elder''', M.D., is a Russian-American professional [[trading|trader]] and a teacher of traders<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.eurekers.com/alexander-elder-de-medico-del-regimen-sovietico-a-maestro-del-psicotrading|title=Alexander Elder: de m\u00e9dico en el r\u00e9gimen sovi\u00e9tico a maestro del psicotrading en EE.UU|last=Barba|first=Cristina|access-date=2018-08-21|language=es}}</ref>. He is the author of ''Trading for a Living'', considered a modern classic among traders.{{fact|date=May 2018}} First published in 1993, this international [[best-seller]]{{fact|date=May 2018}}\nhas been translated into more than a dozen languages and is being used to educate traders around the\nworld. His ''Come into My Trading Room: A Complete Guide to Trading'' was named a 2002 [[Barron's_(newspaper)|Barron\u2019s]] Book\nof the Year. His ''Entries & Exits: Visits to 16 Trading Rooms' was named a 2007 [[SFO Magazine]] Book of the\nYear. His latest book is ''The New Sell & Sell Short: How to Take Profits, Cut Losses, and Benefit from Price\nDeclines'' (2011).\n\nElder was born in [[Saint_Petersburg|Leningrad]] and grew up in [[Estonia]], where he entered medical school at the age of 16.{{fact|date=May 2018}} At 23, while working as a ship\u2019s doctor, he jumped a Soviet ship in [[Africa]] and received political\nasylum in the United States. He worked as a psychiatrist in [[New York City]] and taught at [[Columbia University]]. His experience as a psychiatrist provided him with unique insight into the psychology of trading.\n\n==Publications==\n*Elder, Alexander, ''The New Sell and Sell Short: How to Take Profits, Cutting Losses, and Benefit from Price Declines.'' Hoboken, N.J.: Wiley, 2011. {{ISBN|978-0-470-63239-0}}, revised edition of his ''Sell and Sell Short.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley & Sons, 2008. {{ISBN|978-0-470-18167-6}}\n*Elder, Alexander. ''Entries & Exits: Visits to Sixteen Trading Rooms.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley, 2006. {{ISBN|978-0-471-67805-2}}\n**translated into French as ''Entr\u00e9es et sorties : visite guid\u00e9e de seize salles de trading'' Publisher:\tHendaye [France] : Valor, 2007 {{ISBN|978-2-909356-64-8}}\n*Elder, Alexander, ''Straying From The Flock - Travels in New Zealand.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley, 2005. {{ISBN|0-471-71863-7}}\n*Elder, Alexander. ''Rubles to Dollars: Making Money on Russia's Exploding Financial Frontier.'' New York: New York Institute of Finance, 1999. {{ISBN|978-0-7352-0062-3}}\n*Elder, Alexander.'' Trading for a Living: Psychology, Trading Tactics, Money Management.'' New York: J. Wiley, 1993. {{ISBN|978-0-471-59224-2}} Held in 342 libraries according to [[WorldCat]] <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/trading-for-a-living-psychology-trading-tactics-money-management/oclc/26852630&referer=brief_results]</ref>  \n**Translated into Chinese as ''\u4ee5\u4ea4\u6613\u4e3a\u751f / Yi jiao yi wei sheng'' \u673a\u68b0\u5de5\u4e1a\u51fa\u7248\u793e, Beijing : Ji xie gong ye chu ban she, 2010  {{ISBN|978-7-111-30251-3}}\n**Translated into Spanish as ''Vivir del trading : psicolog\u00eda, t\u00e1cticas de trading, gesti\u00f3n del dinero'' Espa\u00f1a : IdeasPropias], 2004 {{ISBN|978-84-9745-079-9}}\n**Translated into Polish as ''Zaw\u00f3d inwestor gie\u0142dowy : psychologia rynk\u00f3w, taktyka inwestycyjna, zarz\u0105dzanie portfelem'' 1998, {{ISBN|978-83-87286-35-4}}\n**Translated into French as ''Vivre du Trading : psychologie, tactiques de trading, money management''\n*Elder, Alexander. ''Come into My Trading Room A Complete Guide to Trading.''{{ISBN|0471225401}} New York: Wiley, 2002. Study guide for this book is {{ISBN|978-0-471-22540-9}} Held in 832 libraries according to WorldCat <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/come-into-my-trading-room-a-complete-guide-to-trading/oclc/51209940&referer=brief_results]</ref>  \n**Translated into French as ''Entrez dans ma salle de trading : guide de trading complet'' Hendaye : Valor \u00e9d., DL 2004 {{ISBN|978-2-909356-37-2}}\n**Translated into Russian as ''\u0422\u0440\u0435\u0439\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u0441 \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043c \u042d\u043b\u0434\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043c : \u044d\u043d\u0446\u0438\u043a\u043b\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0434\u0438\u044f \u0431\u0438\u0440\u0436\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b /Tre\u012dding s doktorom \u0116lderom : \u0117nt\ufe20s\ufe21iklopedii\ufe20a\ufe21 birzhevo\u012d igry''2010\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.elder.com}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Elder, Alexander}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Date of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American finance and investment writers]]\n[[Category:Soviet defectors]]\n[[Category:People from Saint Petersburg]]\n[[Category:University of Tartu alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{about||the nineteenth-century settler and politician in colonial South Australia|Alexander Lang Elder|the Northern Irish footballer|Alex Elder}}\n<!-- Unsourced image removed: [[File:Alexander_elder.jpg|300px|right]] -->\n'''Alexander Elder''', M.D., is a Russian-American professional [[trading|trader]] and a teacher of traders<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.eurekers.com/alexander-elder-de-medico-del-regimen-sovietico-a-maestro-del-psicotrading|title=Alexander Elder: de m\u00e9dico en el r\u00e9gimen sovi\u00e9tico a maestro del psicotrading en EE.UU|last=Barba|first=Cristina|access-date=2018-08-21|language=es}}</ref>. He is the author of ''Trading for a Living'', considered a modern classic among traders.{{fact|date=May 2018}} First published in 1993, this international [[best-seller]]{{fact|date=May 2018}}\nhas been translated into more than a dozen languages and is being used to educate traders around the\nworld. His ''Come into My Trading Room: A Complete Guide to Trading'' was named a 2002 [[Barron's_(newspaper)|Barron\u2019s]] Book\nof the Year. His ''Entries & Exits: Visits to 16 Trading Rooms' was named a 2007 SFO Magazine Book of the\nYear. His latest book is ''The New Sell & Sell Short: How to Take Profits, Cut Losses, and Benefit from Price\nDeclines'' (2011).\n\nElder was born in [[Saint_Petersburg|Leningrad]] and grew up in [[Estonia]], where he entered medical school at the age of 16.{{fact|date=May 2018}} At 23, while working as a ship\u2019s doctor, he jumped a Soviet ship in [[Africa]] and received political\nasylum in the United States. He worked as a psychiatrist in [[New York City]] and taught at [[Columbia University]]. His experience as a psychiatrist provided him with unique insight into the psychology of trading.\n\n==Publications==\n*Elder, Alexander, ''The New Sell and Sell Short: How to Take Profits, Cutting Losses, and Benefit from Price Declines.'' Hoboken, N.J.: Wiley, 2011. {{ISBN|978-0-470-63239-0}}, revised edition of his ''Sell and Sell Short.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley & Sons, 2008. {{ISBN|978-0-470-18167-6}}\n*Elder, Alexander. ''Entries & Exits: Visits to Sixteen Trading Rooms.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley, 2006. {{ISBN|978-0-471-67805-2}}\n**translated into French as ''Entr\u00e9es et sorties : visite guid\u00e9e de seize salles de trading'' Publisher:\tHendaye [France] : Valor, 2007 {{ISBN|978-2-909356-64-8}}\n*Elder, Alexander, ''Straying From The Flock - Travels in New Zealand.'' Hoboken, N.J.: John Wiley, 2005. {{ISBN|0-471-71863-7}}\n*Elder, Alexander. ''Rubles to Dollars: Making Money on Russia's Exploding Financial Frontier.'' New York: New York Institute of Finance, 1999. {{ISBN|978-0-7352-0062-3}}\n*Elder, Alexander.'' Trading for a Living: Psychology, Trading Tactics, Money Management.'' New York: J. Wiley, 1993